        <updateDate>2021-05-20T13:46:49Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Responsible Additions and Increases to Sustain Employee Health Benefits Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill modifies the tax exclusion for distributions from health flexible spending arrangements provided to employees under a cafeteria plan to (1) increase the annual limit on employee salary reduction contributions to $5,000, with an additional $500 for each additional employee dependent above two dependents that has not been taken into account by another person for the year; (2) revise the adjustment for inflation after 2021; and (3) allow a carryforward into the next year for unused amounts in such plans.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
